The Germania was published about the same year; this work has been regarded as a satire on Roman life by contrast with an idealized picture of the Germans, and also as a warning of the dangers to the Empire from such a simple and vigorous nation on its borders.

The Materies, the materials for which he must have been long collecting, were probably published in the earlier part of Trajan's reign (98-117); they contained the history of the Empire from 69—96, Galba to Domitian, in fourteen bookS, of which only four books and a portion of' the fifth remain to us.
